gomodel:SYNGO_4817  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: Otoferlin (OTOF) binds calcium ions and interacts with Syntaxin1 and SNAP25\n\nFigure 5: auditory inner hair cell (IHC) ribbon synapses develop normally in Oterfilin -/- mice\n\nFigure 6,S6: Calcium-triggered exocytosis is almost completely abolished in the absence of Otoferlin. Experimental description: M&M: \"Electron Microscopy. Mouse cochleas were fixed as described\"\n\nantibody:\n\nAuthors used 3 different antibodies against OTOF throughout this study, the N14 antibody was used for EM.\n\nFrom supplemental M&M: \"Two rabbit polyclonal antibodies and one mouse monoclonal antibody were generated against mouse otoferlin. The N14 immune serum was raised against the synthetic peptide GKTRSHKEEPQRQDEP (aa 196-211) located in the C2A-C2B interdomain, and the corresponding antibodies were affinity-purified.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4817" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

